cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for visual tracking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel scheme to learn target-aware features, which involves developing a regression loss and a ranking loss to guide the generation of target-active and scale-sensitive features. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses a Siamese matching network for visual tracking, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
